#Binomial Heaps implementation

##How to compile and run

bash
g++ -o app Main.cpp
./app


Insert key — inserts a single integer into the heap
Insert multiple keys — inserts several space-separated keys at once
Find minimum — returns the smallest key without removing it
Extract minimum — removes and returns the minimum key, then restructures the heap
Decrease key — decreases the value of an existing node and restores the heap property
Delete node — deletes a node by key using decrease-key followed by extract-min
Print heap — displays each Binomial Tree in the heap with its full structure
Print root list — shows the root list ordered by degree (B0, B1, B2, ...)
Load demo data — inserts 12 preset keys to explore the structure right away
Exit — exit
